truth: Hey, Mark. 
mark: Oh, Truth. 
mark: You been good lately? 
truth: [color=#e85670][i]Mark doesn’t flinch. Never does.[/i]
truth: [color=#e85670][i]He looks straight at me—like he’s trying to read something off my face.[/i]
truth: Yeah man, what's up?
mark: Nothing bro, it's just you're... you, haha. 
truth: [color=#e85670][i]There it is...[/i]
mark: You're on a different planet sometimes. 
mark: Like you're looking at some shit the rest of us can't even see. 
truth: If you're gonna be a dickhead, just say it straight. 
mark: It's all love, man.
truth: [color=#e85670][i]I don't feel like coming up with a witty response.[/i]
[signal arg="mark_intro_complete"]
truth: I also wanted to talk about something serious. 
mark: Damn, you suddenly sound intense. What's up? 
truth: That night. The 13th.
mark: ...What about it?
truth: [color=#e85670][i]It’s been bothering me.[/i][/color]
truth: [color=#e85670][i]Not what happened.[/i][/color]
truth: [color=#e85670][i]What I can’t remember.[/i][/color]
mark: Dude... we just hung out, didn’t we?
truth: Yeah.
truth: That’s what I thought too.
truth: But think about it.
truth: We went out.
truth: There was a blackout.
mark: Yeah, there was that. But so what? 
truth: Then after, that loud noise.
truth: And after that?
mark: ...
mark: I mean... nothing? We left?
truth: Exactly. 
truth: Something's off. 
truth: Something happened in that gap, right after the lights went out.
truth: And nobody knows. 
mark: ...
mark: Okay.
mark: So what, you wanna play detective now?
truth: [color=#e85670][i]This guy...[/i][/color]
truth: I'm not gonna "play". 
truth: I'll prove it. 
truth: I'm going to reconstruct that night. 
truth: Piece by piece.
mark: ...
truth: I want everyone in the living room later.
mark: Everyone?
truth: Yeah.